# Hospital Login Tool - Walkthrough

I have created the automation tool for you. Since this tool interacts with your local hospital systems, you will need to run it on your machine.

## Prerequisites

1.  **Python**: Ensure Python is installed.
2.  **Dependencies**: Open a terminal in the project folder and run:
    ```powershell
    pip install -r requirements.txt
    playwright install
    ```

## How to Run

1.  Navigate to the project directory:
    ```powershell
    cd C:\Users\A03772\.gemini\antigravity\scratch\hospital_login_tool
    ```
2.  Run the main application:
    ```powershell
    python main.py
    ```
3.  A window will appear asking for your Username and Password.
4.  Enter your credentials and click **Login**.

## What to Expect

-   **Web System**: A browser window will open, navigate to `http://10.10.246.80/Ipo/HISLogin`, and attempt to log in.
-   **HIS System**: The tool will launch [C:\VGHTC\HISLogin.exe](file:///VGHTC/HISLogin.exe) and attempt to type your credentials.

## Troubleshooting

-   **Web Login Fails**: If the browser opens but doesn't type, the "selectors" (HTML IDs) might be different. You may need to inspect the webpage (Right click -> Inspect) and update [web_login.py](file:///C:/Users/A03772/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/hospital_login_tool/web_login.py) with the correct `name="..."` or `id="..."` for the username/password fields.
-   **HIS Login Fails**: If the app opens but doesn't type, the window title might not match. Check [his_login.py](file:///C:/Users/A03772/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/hospital_login_tool/his_login.py) and adjust the `title_re=".*Login.*"` regex to match the actual window title of your HIS app.
